race.description: Aust National Field Days 23rd-25th Oct Maiden Plate
race.comment: REAL BAKER (7) debuts for Bjorn Baker and the barn strikes at 32% at this venue. Was a big trial winner at Wyong and missed a nose at Rosehill the one after. Has an awkward gate but expect him to be good enough to manage. TOMCAT FLOWERS (3) resumed further improved beaten 2L at Goulburn and then was well bet again at Canberra and had excuses at the business end when he led. Fitter again and rates well. MILLY MOLLY MANDY (5) resumed and stuck on well when placing second behind a dominant winner over 1200m at Nowra. Showed good early speed and has more to give. Strips fitter and will be hard to beat in a suitable race. CAMILLA (4) can improve for the Snowden stable over the longer sprint. Finally draws an inside gate and Sherry rides for the first time.
